NEWS THIS MORNING

The stock market liked that news:

Via STAT News's Adam Feurstein and Matthew Herper, an experimental antiviral medicine given to patients in Chicago has resulted in a drop in fever and respiratory symptoms in almost all of the patients who took the drug. https://bit.ly/2XKac5a

The drug: Remdesivir from Gilead Sciences, Inc.

The size of the study: "University of Chicago Medicine recruited 125 people with Covid-19 into Gilead's two Phase 3 clinical trials. Of those people, 113 had severe disease. All the patients have been treated with daily infusions of remdesivir."

From the infectious disease specialist who is overseeing the study: "The best news is that most of our patients have already been discharged, which is great. We've only had two patients perish."

The full story: https://bit.ly/2XKac5a

REACTION -- THE STOCK MARKET ROSE THIS MORNING:

The market jumped this morning following the report of success in treating coronavirus patients with an experimental antiviral drug. https://bit.ly/2XIHJNd

The numbers this morning: "The Dow Jones Industrial Average was up 550 points, or 2.3 percent, while the S&P 500 rose 52 points, or 1.8 percent."

